.TH ISOCMD 1 "April 2026" "Iso Commander 6.3.5" "Iso-Commander Manual"

.SH NAME
Iso Commander (isocmd) \- Command-line utility for managing .iso files and converting image formats.

.SH DESCRIPTION
Iso Commander (isocmd) is a command-line utility for managing .iso files and converting various image formats to .iso using asynchronous I/O operations and multi-threaded processing.

.SH NON-INTERACTIVE COMMANDS
.TP
.B -v, --version
.br
Show program version.

.TP
.B --silent
.br
Suppress informational, error and warning output.

.TP
.B -d\<N\>
.br
Set max directory recursion depth when scanning for ISOs; default is -1 (unlimited).

.TP
.B mount
.br
Mount one or more ISO files or directories containing ISOs. Requires root.

.TP
.B umount, unmount
.br
Unmount ISO mount points. Without arguments or with "all", unmounts all under /mnt. Requires root.

.SH UI INTERACTIVE OPTIONS AND FEATURES
.TP
.B ManageISO
Mount, Umount, Delete, Move, Copy, and Write ISO files. Note that Write retains bootable status for USB drives. Requires root for mount/write operations.

.TP
.B Convert2ISO
Converts .bin, .img, .mdf, and .nrg files to .iso. Ported from original C tools (mdf2iso, nrg2iso, ccd2iso).

.TP
.B ImportISO
Creates and updates a local ISO database. The database is capped at approximately \fB10,000 entries\fR or a \fB1MB file size limit\fR to ensure rapid filtering performance.

.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file is located at \fI~/.config/isocmd/config\fR. It uses a simple \fIkey = value\fR format.

.SS GENERAL SETTINGS
.TP
.B auto_update
Enable background metadata updates from folder history upon startup. 
.br
Values: on, off (Default: off)
.TP
.B filenames_only
Display only filenames instead of full paths. This acts as a global override for all list display modes except for the unmount list.
.br
Values: on, off (Default: on)
.TP
.B pagination
Items per page in list view.
.br
Values: integer >= 0 (Default: 25). Set to 0 to disable.

.SS THEME SETTINGS
.TP
.B menu_color
Sets the accent color for menus and headers.
.br
Values: green, cyan, white (Default: white)
.TP
.B list_theme
Defines the color palette used for displaying lists.
.br
Values: original, classic, high_contrast, neon, ocean, sunset, forest, midnight, mono, retro, crimson, dracula (Default: original)

.SS HISTORY SETTINGS
.TP
.B folder_path_history_lines
Max unique folder paths to persist in history. (Default: 30)
.TP
.B filter_history_lines
Max unique search filters to persist in history. (Default: 15)

.SS DISPLAY SETTINGS
Controls whether lists are shown in \fBfull\fR (detailed) or \fBcompact\fR format. 
.br
\fBNote:\fR If \fBfilenames_only\fR is enabled, path details will be stripped regardless of these settings.
.IP
\fBmount_list\fR (Default: compact)
.br
\fBumount_list\fR (Default: full)
.br
\fBcp_mv_rm_list\fR (Default: compact)
.br
\fBwrite_list\fR (Default: compact)
.br
\fBconversion_lists\fR (Default: compact)

.SS THREAD SETTINGS
Iso Commander utilizes a multi-threaded architecture to optimize I/O-heavy operations and UI responsiveness.
.TP
.B max_thread_cap
Global maximum concurrent threads allowed. (Default: 32)
.TP
.B threads_for_cp_mv
Threads allocated for copy/move tasks. (Default: 8)
.TP
.B threads_for_conversions
Threads allocated for ISO file conversions. (Default: 8)
.TP
.B threads_for_mount
Threads allocated for mounting tasks. (Default: 16)
.TP
.B threads_for_umount
Threads allocated for unmounting tasks. (Default: 32)
.TP
.B threads_for_database_cleanup
Threads allocated for database maintenance and synchronization. (Default: 16)
.TP
.B threads_for_rm
Threads allocated for file removal tasks. (Default: 32)
.TP
.B threads_for_list_sorting / threads_for_list_filtering
Threads allocated for UI responsiveness during sorting and filtering. (Default: 4)

.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/isocmd/config
Primary configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/isocmd/database/iso_commander_database.txt
The main ISO metadata database.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/isocmd/database/iso_commander_path_database.txt
Persistent history of accessed folder paths.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/isocmd/database/iso_commander_filter_database.txt
Persistent history of search filter terms.

